The paper focuses on developing a deep learning framework for click-through rate (CTR) prediction in recommender systems. This involves learning sophisticated feature interactions behind user behaviors, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "learning to rank" in information retrieval (IR). The proposed framework combines the power of factorization machines (FM) and deep learning, which are both popular techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also conducts comprehensive experiments on benchmark and commercial data, which involves data analysis and manipulation techniques commonly used in data science (DS) and database (DB) research. Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Science), and cs.DB (Database).
